# API Patterns

## View conventions

- Public views: `generics.ListAPIView` / `RetrieveAPIView`, `permission_classes = [AllowAny]`
- Authenticated views: `generics.ListCreateAPIView` / `RetrieveUpdateDestroyAPIView`, `permission_classes = [IsAuthenticated]`
- Admin CRUD views: same generics pattern but `permission_classes = [IsAdminUser]`
- Always scope user-owned data: `get_queryset` must filter by `user=self.request.user`
- Use `get_object_or_404` with compound lookups (slug + number) for content endpoints
- Always add `@extend_schema(tags=['Tag Name'])` for Swagger documentation

## Serializer categories

| Category         | Naming                    | Use case                       |
|------------------|---------------------------|--------------------------------|
| Read (public)    | `QuestionReadSerializer`  | Frontend consumption, camelCase |
| Write (admin)    | `QuestionWriteSerializer` | Admin CRUD, snake_case          |
| Staged           | `StagedRequestSerializer` | Staged request payloads         |
| User-scoped      | `HighlightSerializer`     | Per-user data                   |

## URL conventions

| Prefix             | Auth        | Purpose                              |
|--------------------|-------------|--------------------------------------|
| `/api/subjects/`   | None        | Public content (read-only)           |
| `/api/auth/`       | None/Bearer | Registration, login, token refresh   |
| `/api/manage/`     | Admin       | Direct CRUD on content models        |
| `/api/staged/`     | Bearer      | Staged request workflow              |
| `/api/highlights/` | Bearer      | User highlights                      |
| `/api/notes/`      | Bearer      | User notes                           |
| `/api/schema/`     | None        | OpenAPI schema                       |
| `/api/docs/`       | None        | Swagger UI                           |
| `/api/redoc/`      | None        | ReDoc                                |

## Staged request payload shape

```json
{
  "operation": "create | update | delete",
  "target_model": "subject | chapter | question | takeaway",
  "target_id": null,
  "payload": { "field": "value" }
}
```

- `target_id` is null for create, required for update/delete
- `payload` contains model fields as key-value pairs
- For create: payload has all required fields (e.g., `chapter_id`, `question`, `answer`)
- For update: payload has only the fields to change
- For delete: payload is empty `{}`

## Filtering

- Use query params for list filtering: `?subject=slug&chapter=number&status=pending`
- Parse in `get_queryset`, not in the serializer
- Return empty list (not 404) when no matches

## Error responses

- Use DRF's built-in error formatting (400 with field-level errors)
- Custom errors: return `Response({"detail": "message"}, status=XXX)`
- Staged request errors: "Request is already approved/rejected" on double action
- Never expose internal details (tracebacks, SQL) in error responses

## DeltaMails endpoints

| Method | Endpoint                           | Auth     | Description                            |
|--------|------------------------------------|----------|----------------------------------------|
| GET    | /api/deltamails/                   | Optional | List subscriptions (by user or ?email) |
| POST   | /api/deltamails/subscribe/         | Optional | Create subscriptions (multi-subject)   |
| PATCH  | /api/deltamails/{id}/preferences/  | JWT      | Update difficulty / custom_prompt      |
| POST   | /api/deltamails/unsubscribe/       | No       | Deactivate by email + subject slug     |
